="t mb41 x29 h27 y1ecf ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Following the feast for the princes, what other feast was given </div><div class="t m647 x27 h27 y1053 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by the king? At the same time what did Queen Vashti do? Verses </div><div class="t m66a x27 h27 y63e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5-9. </div><div class="t m2b6 x4a h27 y219c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m8a x29 h27 y219c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What command did the king send to the queen on the seventh </div><div class="t m1180 x27 h27 y1d58 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">day of the feast? When she refused to come, with whom did the king </div><div class="t m263 x27 h27 y13c5 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in his wrath take counsel? Following the advice of his counselors, </div><div class="t m1085 x27 h27 y1bb4 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">what decree was sent throughout the kingdom? Why? Verses 10-22. </div><div class="t mcd2 x42 h60 y1e74 ff6 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Esther Chosen Queen </div><div class="t ma2 x4a h27 y17c0 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m9a4 x29 h27 y111c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Later when the king&apos;s anger was appeased, what plan was </div><div class="t m687 x11 h27 y217b ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">proposed by the king&apos;s servants? What Jew is mentioned as living </div><div class="t m63b x11 h27 y159b ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in Shushan? Whom had he brought up as a daughter? Esther 2:1-7. </div><div class="t m1cd x14 h27 y17c6 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m781 x29 h27 y1e33 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When Esther was brought to the king&apos;s house how was she </div><div class="t m1754 x11 h27 y19cd ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">received? What shows Mordecai&apos;s deep interest in Esther at this </div><div class="t m3d1 x11 h27 y1ef6 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">time? What was the result when she appeared before the king? </div><div class="t m1958 x11 h27 y2199 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 8-17. </div><div class="t m2817 x2a h2b y2259 ff4 f